period setting, they devote most of the book to a multiperiod context, which adds the long-term perspective most risk management analyses require. Each chapter concludes with a discussion of the relevant literature and a set of problems. The book presents a thoroughly accessible introduction to risk, bridging the gap between the traditionally separate economics and finance literatures.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aEconomics -- Decision making. 0aEconomicsxDecision making. 0aFinance -- Decision making. 0aFinancexDecision making. 0aRisk assessment. 0aRisk management. 0aRisk. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Economics / Theory.2bisacsh1 aEeckhoudt, Louis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGollier, Christian, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aGollier, Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchlesinger, Harris, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSchlesinger, Harris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044250240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781400829217zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781400829217423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781400829217.jpg  a978-3-11-044250-2  Princeton University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK